        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>Ch. tells me to say that he has been much pleased with your notice of his views &amp; he thinks you have given it very correctly as far as a few words could do so. As far as he remembers you are the sole person, except pure naturalists, who have noticed this part with any approbation. He has lately been going over the chapter with much care, after rereading all the many hostile criticisms, &amp; has slightly modified parts, giving somewhat more force to the influence of the approbation or disapprobation of others; but he still remains convinced about his fundamental notion<ref target="#foot.f2"/> <lb resp="#mjhawkins"/></p>
<p>As you are great at decyphering dear Snow I have sent it as it is— wh will shock Ch.<ref target="#foot.f3"/></p> 
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="tnotes">
                <note xml:id="tnote.n1">1.1 tells … he] <hi rend="italic">interl</hi> </note>
                <note xml:id="tnote.n2">1.2 it] <hi rend="italic">interl</hi> </note>
                <note xml:id="tnote.n3">1.2 As] <hi rend="italic">over</hi> ‘so’ </note>
                <note xml:id="tnote.n4">1.4 part] <hi rend="italic">above del</hi> ‘point’ </note>
                <note xml:id="tnote.n5">1.6 somewhat] <hi rend="italic">interl</hi> </note>
                <note xml:id="tnote.n6">1.7 others;] <hi rend="italic">over</hi> ‘,’ </note>
                <note xml:id="tnote.n7">1.7 remains … his] <hi rend="italic">above del</hi> ‘<hi rend="italic">[</hi>tho<hi rend="italic">]</hi> maintains retain the case’ </note>
